Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.206, 37. Name Xenophantos. Perhaps to be equated with British Museum 1925,0119.288, despite the different length of line 2 in Petrie's drawing.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0713)
